originalText.text:
I used to work here and Ken Markel is abusive to patients and staff.  He literally ties kids down in the room and completely traumatizes them. As a mother, if anyone treated my child the way I have seen him treat patients, I would file assault charges. Please do NOT take your child here.

However, the other dentists that worked there were much better and never treated patients like that.

originalText.text: Beware of predatory pricing and unethical practices in addition to zero customer service. Three years after my kids visited they sent a bill for $181 without providing justification and threatening to take to collections. Dr Ken Markel never responded to requests for clarification. A place to seriously avoid!

originalText.text: I brought my children to this practice at the recommendation of our family dentist. They told me that our prophylactic exams and sealant placements were 100% covered by insurance, so I authorized them to go ahead. Then I received a bill in the mail for $1400 dollars. When I called to dispute the bill, I was told by the highly unprofessional person who answered the phone that, yes, my insurance covers 100% but that "they didn't like the amount that they received." So they decided to mark up the prices and pass it along to the patient. Unbelievable. Unprofessional. Will never return.
